                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus/><div style="margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:&#10;normal"><span style="font-size: small;"><span>Fol. 4v: Donation note.</span></span></div><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 115%;">Fol. 4v: </span></span><span style="font-size: large;"><span style="line-height: 115%;">&#4829;&#4632;&#4925;&#4624;&#4941;&#5011;</span><span style="line-height: 115%;"> &#4824;&#4723;&#4710;&#4720;&#5011; &#4925;&#4846;&#4757;&#5011; &#4824;&#4608;&#4872;&#4648;&#5011; &#4656;&#4635;&#4829;&#5011; &#4824;&#4813;&#4773;&#4721;&#5011; &#4885;&#4622;&#5011; &#4632;&#4624;&#4851;&#5011; &#4824;&#4808;&#4608;&#4707;&#5011; &#4773;&#4651;&#4661;&#5011; &#4768;&#4653;&#4768;&#4843;&#5011; &#4645;&#4619;&#4660;&#5011; &#4808;&#4621;&#4849;&#5011; &#4808;&#4941;&#4673;&#4649;&#5011; &#4616;&#4757;&#4873;&#4640;&#5011; &#4752;&#4872;&#4645;&#4725;&#5011; &#4846;&#4624;&#4757;&#4661;&#5011; &#4757;&#4873;&#4640;&#5011; &#4824;&#4770;&#4725;&#4846;&#4917;&#4843;&#5011; &#4776;&#4632;&#5011; &#4845;&#4777;&#4758;&#5011; &#4616;&#4632;&#4853;&#4739;&#4754;&#4720;&#5011; &#4752;&#4941;&#4661;&#5011; &#4808;&#4645;&#4875;&#5011; &#4768;&#4636;&#4757;&#5011; &#4808;&#4768;&#4636;&#4757;&#4962; &#4824;&#4656;&#4648;&#4678;&#5011; &#4808;&#4824;&#4936;&#4624;&#4678;&#5011; &#4704;&#4645;&#4621;&#4899;&#4752;&#5011; &#4916;&#4901;&#4654;&#4661;&#5011; &#4808;&#4915;&#4813;&#4622;&#4661;&#5011; &#4813;&#4873;&#4824;&#5011; &#4616;&#4845;&#4777;&#4757;&#4962; </span></span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"><p><span unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;Arial">Fol. 4v: This book of the church of &#7778;&#477;yon of the </span><span unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;Arial">country of S&#228;maz, which is Gw&#477;lo M&#228;&#7717;&#228;da, was donated by </span><span unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;Arial">&#704;Ar&#704;aya &#346;&#477;llase, a son and beloved one of </span><span unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;Arial">Yo&#7717;ann&#477;s</span><span unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;Arial"> the King of Kings of Ethiopia, so that it might be for him the salvation of the soul and the flesh. Amen. </span><span unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;Arial">May the one who stole and who erased (its text) be excommunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul.</span></p></q>
                           <p>Written in red ink. The note dates to the time of ʾArʾaya Śǝllase (b.1869/70, d. 1888), a son of King Yoḥannǝs IV (r. 1872-89). The note named the nowadays church of Maryam, as the church of Ṣǝyon (s. also Additio 2).</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small;">Fol. 214v: Inventory of the items donated by different individuals to the church of S&#228;maz.</span></p><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 115%;">Fol. 214v: </span></span><span style="font-size: large;"><span style="line-height: 115%;">&#4971;</span><span style="line-height: 115%;">&#4725;&#5011; &#4672;&#4634;&#4661;&#5011; &#4808;&#4653;&#4677;&#5011; &#4824;&#4710;&#5011; &#4971;&#4725;&#5011; &#4808;&#4653;&#4677;&#5011;</span><span style="line-height: 115%;"> &#4824;&#4710;&#5011; &#4704;&#4653;&#4758;&#4661;&#5011; &#4609;&#4616;&#4725;&#5011; &#4624;&#4653;&#5011; &#4704;&#4653;&#4758;&#4661;&#5011; &#4969;&#4877;&#4661;&#4619;&#5011;</span><span style="line-height: 115%;">&#4969;&#4632;&#4661;&#4672;&#4621;&#4962; &#4969; &#4637;&#4757;&#4923;&#4941;&#5011; &#4969;&#4661;&#4821;&#4621;&#5011; &#4637;&#4661;&#4616;&#5011; &#4941;&#4673;&#4653; &#4808;&#4621;&#4851;&#4962;</span><span style="line-height: 115%;">&#8230;</span>&#160;</span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 115%;">Fol. 214v: 3 decorated tunics, 3 decorated mantels, two silk mantels, 1 panther (mantel), 1 cross; 1 carpet, 1 icon with Her beloved son&#8230;</span></span></p></q>
                           <p>The note is written in Gәʿәz, Amharic and Tǝgrǝñña. 
The donors of the items are Rämḥa Śǝllase and ʾArʾaya Śǝllase; the name Yoḥannǝs Käma is mentioned in the note, but is not clear whether it refers to the name of the church or to a name of an individual; the keeper (gäbäz) is Wäldä Gäbrәʾel. The note named the nowadays church of Maryam, as the church of Ṣǝyon (s. also Additio 1).</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The scribe did not use the bottom ruled line on fols. 5r-28v.&#xD;
- Excerpts from hymns for the Good Friday (?) have benn added in the upper margin of in fols. 133rv, 134r, 140rv, 141r, 162rv, 175rv.&#xD;
- Some lines of the text are framed: fols. 21va (the last six ls.), 137vb (ls. 14-17).&#xD;
- Some words are added in the margins of some fols.: ʾǝllä yǝṣäbbǝʿǝwwomu lä-däqiqä ʾƎsraʾel (fol. 56v, upper margin, top of column b); bä-hägärä (fol. 79v, upper margin, top of column a); bä-ʾǝntä zä-kǝḥdä Ṗeṭros (fol. 121r, upper margin, top of column c, rubricated).&#xD;
- The title of the work "Mäṣḥafä dorho" is written in the upper margin of fol. 75r, top of column a, framed and rubricated. &#xD;
- The title of the work "Laḥa Maryam" is written in the upper margin of fol. 153v, top of column c, rubricated. &#xD;
- The name of Mary is written in “negative” writing: “white” (colour of the parchment) writing on black ink background obtained, in this case, by leaving blank the space for the letter (s. EAE III, 741) (fol. 214rc).&#xD;
- A recent addition under the colophon, in blue pen, with admixture of Tǝgrǝñña (?), mentions a name: fol. 214rc, ḍäḥafǝʾu g/ğata Kaśa "the scribe is gra geta Kaśa".&#xD;
- Erased words: e.g., fols. 141rb l.18, 61r (top of the left margin).&#xD;
- Omitted words or corrections are written interlineally: fols. 9ra, 38va, 60rc, 103va, 154vb, 202ra.&#xD;
- Pen trial (?) in the bottom margin of fol. 6r, rubricated.</item>
